import pickle
n_images = len(file_names)
final_features = {}
for i, path in enumerate(file_names, 1):
    image_path = os.path.join(output_dir, path)
    if os.path.exists(image_path):
        img = cv2.imread(image_path)
        if img is not None:
            img = cv2.resize(img, (299, 299))  # Resize image for Xception
            x = np.expand_dims(img, axis=0)
            x = preprocess_input(x)

            # Extract features using Xception model
            features = xception_model.predict(x, verbose=0)
            final_features[path] = features.flatten()

            print(f"\r{i} of {n_images} images processed", end='')  # Print progress
        else:
            print(f"Failed to read image: {image_path}")
    else:
        print(f"Image not found: {image_path}")
print("\nTotal number of images processed:", len(final_features))
print("Shape of one feature vector:", final_features[file_names[0]].shape)
with open('/content/drive/MyDrive/OPSM325/final_features_xception.pickle', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(final_features, f)

# Match images with their corresponding captions
file_captions = []
file_features = []

for caption in captions:
    file_name = caption.split("\t")[0][:-2]
    file_text = caption.split("\t")[1]

    if file_name in final_features.keys():
        file_captions.append(file_text)
        file_features.append(final_features[file_name])
In [ ]:
# Tokenize captions
def tokenize(sentences):
    tokenizer = Tokenizer()
    tokenizer.fit_on_texts(sentences)
    return tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(sentences), tokenizer

captions_tokenized, caption_tokenizer = tokenize(file_captions)
In [ ]:
# Pad tokenized sequences
max_caption_len = max(len(seq) for seq in captions_tokenized)
padded_captions = pad_sequences(captions_tokenized, maxlen=max_caption_len, padding='post')

# Reshape padded sequences
padded_captions = padded_captions.reshape(*padded_captions.shape, 1)
In [ ]:

In [ ]:
# Convert data to TensorFlow tensors
def convert_to_tensors(x, y, batch_size):
    data_tensor = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((x, y))
    data_tensor = data_tensor.cache()
    data_tensor = data_tensor.shuffle(1000, reshuffle_each_iteration=True)
    data_tensor = data_tensor.batch(batch_size, drop_remainder=True)
    return data_tensor

batch_size = 128
train_data = convert_to_tensors(X_train, y_train, batch_size)
test_data = convert_to_tensors(X_test, y_test, batch_size)
In [ ]:
# Define model architecture
input_sequence = Input(shape=(2048,))

r_vec = RepeatVector(max_caption_len)(input_sequence)

decoder1 = LSTM(256, return_sequences=True, kernel_regularizer=tf.keras.regularizers.l2(), dropout=0.2)(r_vec)
decoder2 = LSTM(128, return_sequences=True, kernel_regularizer=tf.keras.regularizers.l2())(decoder1)
decoder3 = LSTM(64, return_sequences=True, kernel_regularizer=tf.keras.regularizers.l2())(decoder2)

logits = TimeDistributed(Dense(len(caption_tokenizer.word_index) + 1))(decoder3)

model = Model(input_sequence, Activation('softmax')(logits))

lr_rates = [1e-3, 1e-4, 1e-5]  # Learning rates to try
batch_size = 64  # Batch size
epochs = 10  # Number of epochs
dropout_rate = 0.2  # Dropout rate

best_accuracy = 0
best_hyperparameters = {}

for lr in lr_rates:
    # Compile the model with current hyperparameters
    model.compile(loss=sparse_categorical_crossentropy,
                  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=lr),
                  metrics=['accuracy'])

    # Train the model
    history = model.fit(train_data,
                        validation_data=test_data,
                        epochs=epochs,
                        batch_size=batch_size,
                        shuffle=True,
                        verbose=0)

    # Evaluate the model
    _, accuracy = model.evaluate(test_data, verbose=0)

    # Check if current hyperparameters result in better accuracy
    if accuracy > best_accuracy:
        best_accuracy = accuracy
        best_hyperparameters = {'lr': lr, 'batch_size': batch_size, 'dropout_rate': dropout_rate}

print("Best hyperparameters:", best_hyperparameters)
print("Best accuracy:", best_accuracy)

    index_to_words = {idx: word for word, idx in tokenizer.word_index.items()}
    index_to_words[0] = '<empty>'
    return ' '.join([index_to_words[prediction] for prediction in np.argmax(logits, 1)])
